<subsection xml:id="subsection-1-1-4">
  <title>Exercises</title>

  <exercise xml:id="ex-1-1-1">
    <title>Solving a quadratic equation 1</title>
    <webwork>
      <pg-code>
        Context("Numeric");
        $a = list_random(3,4,5);
        $a2 = $a-1;
        $r1 = list_random(-5..-1,1..5);
        $r2 = list_random(-5..-1,1..5);
        while ($r1 == $r2){
            $r2 = list_random(-5..-1,1..5);
        }
        $b = -($a2)*($r1 + $r2);
        $c = ($a-1)*$r1*$r2;
        $smaller = min($r1, $r2);
        $larger = max($r1, $r2);
        $ans_small = Compute($smaller);
        $ans_large = Compute($larger);
        $a_display = ($a == 1) ? "" : "$a";
        $b_display = ($b &lt; 0) ? "- " . abs($b) : "+ " . $b;
        $c_display = ($c &lt; 0) ? "- " . abs($c) : "+ " . $c;
      </pg-code>

      <statement>
        <p>
          Solve the quadratic equation
          <m><var name="$a_display"/>x^2 <var name = "$b_display"/>x <var name = "$c_display"/> = x^2</m>. 
        </p>

        <p>
            Smaller root:
            <var name = "$ans_small" width = "10"/>
        </p>

        <p>
            Larger root:
            <var name = "$ans_large" width = "10"/>
        </p>
      </statement>

      <solution>
        <p>
            First, we write the equation in the form <m>{ax^2 + bx + c = 0}.</m>  <md><var name = "$a_display"/>x^2 <var name = "$b_display"/>x <var name = "$c_display"/> = 0</md>
        </p>
        <p>
            We can use the quadratic formula:
        </p>

        <p>
            <md> x = \frac{-<var name="$b_display"/> \pm \sqrt{<var name="$b_display"/>^2 - 4(<var name="$a_display"/>)(<var name="$c_display"/>)}}{2(<var name="$a_display"/>)} = <var name = "$r1"/>, <var name = "$r2"/>.</md>
        </p>
      </solution>
    </webwork>
  </exercise>

  <exercise xml:id="ex-1-1-2">
    <title>Solving a radical equation</title>
    <webwork>
        <pg-code><![CDATA[
    Context("Numeric");
    Context()->flags->set(tolType=>"absolute", tolerance=>0.001);

    $a = list_random(2,3,4);
    $b = list_random(1..3);
    $c = list_random(12..16);

    $a2 = $a**2 + 1;
    $b2 = -2*$a*$b;
    $c2 = $b**2 - $c;

    $d = $b2**2 - 4*$a2*$c2;

    while ($d < 0) {
    $a = list_random(2,3,4);
    $b = list_random(1..3);
    $c = list_random(12..16);

    $a2 = $a**2 + 1;
    $b2 = -2*$a*$b;
    $c2 = $b**2 - $c;

    $d = $b2**2 - 4*$a2*$c2;
    }

    $r1 = (-$b2 + sqrt($d))/(2*$a2);
    $r2 = (-$b2 - sqrt($d))/(2*$a2);

    $smaller = min($r1, $r2);
    $larger = max($r1, $r2);

    # For the original radical equation, the larger root is the valid one.
    $ans = Compute($larger);

    $a_display = "$a";
    $b_display = "$b";
    $c_display = "$c";

    $b2_display = ($b2 < 0) ? "- " . abs($b2) : "+ " . $b2;
    $c2_display = ($c2 < 0) ? "- " . abs($c2) : "+ " . $c2;

    $larger_display = sprintf("%.3f", $larger);
    $smaller_display = sprintf("%.3f", $smaller);
        ]]></pg-code>

        <statement>
            <p>
                Solve the following equation. Enter your answer to at least three decimal places.
            </p>

            <p>
                <md>
                    <var name="$a"/>x - \sqrt{<var name="$c"/> - x^2} = <var name="$b"/>
                </md>
            </p>

            <p>
                Solution:
                <var name="$ans" width="10"/>
            </p>
        </statement>

        <solution>
        <p>
            First, isolate the square root term:
        </p>

            <p>
                <md>
                    \begin{aligned}
                    <var name="$a"/>x - \sqrt{<var name="$c"/> - x^2} &amp;= <var name="$b"/> \\
                    -\sqrt{<var name="$c"/> - x^2} &amp;= <var name="$b"/> - <var name="$a"/>x \\
                    \sqrt{<var name="$c"/> - x^2} &amp;= <var name="$a"/>x - <var name="$b"/>
                    \end{aligned}
                </md>
            </p>

            <p>
                Now square both sides:
            </p>
            <p>
                <md>
                    \begin{aligned}
                    <var name="$c"/> - x^2 &amp;= (<var name="$a"/>x - <var name="$b"/>)^2 \\
                    <var name="$c"/> - x^2 &amp;= (<var name="$a"/>^2)x^2 - 2(<var name="$a"/>)(<var name="$b"/>)x + <var name="$b"/>^2 \\
                    <var name="$a2"/>x^2 <var name="$b2_display"/>x <var name="$c2_display"/> &amp;= 0
                    \end{aligned}
                </md>
            </p>

        <p>
            Solving the quadratic gives possible roots.
            <m><var name="$smaller_display"/></m> and
            <m><var name="$larger_display"/></m>.
            The smaller root turns out not to solve the original equation.  So, we have one solution.
            <m><var name="$larger_display"/></m>.
        </p>
        </solution>
        </webwork>
    </exercise>

    <exercise xml:id="ex-1-1-3">
    <title>Solving a hidden quadratic equation</title>
    <webwork>
      <pg-code>
        Context("Numeric");
        Context()->flags->set(tolType=>"absolute", tolerance=>0.001);
        
        $ans_small = Compute(-0.24559);
        $ans_large = Compute(0.10696);
      </pg-code>

      <statement>
        <p>
          Solve the quadratic equation
          <md>4e^{5x} - 2e^{10x} = 1</md>.
        </p>

       <p>
            Smaller solution:
            <var name = "$ans_small" width = "10"/>
        </p>

        <p>
            Larger solution:
            <var name = "$ans_large" width = "10"/>
        </p>
      </statement>

      <solution>
        <p>
            We can make a substitution <m>t = e^{5x}</m>.  Then, we have <m>{4t - 2t^2 = 1}</m>.  We can re-write this as <m>{2t^2 - 4t + 1 = 0.}</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            We can use the quadratic formula:
        </p>

        <p>
            <md> t = \frac{4 \pm \sqrt{16 - 8}}{4} \approx 0.29289, 1.70711.</md>
        </p>

        <p>
            Recall that <m>t=e^{5x}</m>.  So, <m>e^{5x} \approx 0.29289</m> or <m>e^{5x} \approx 1.70711.</m>  
            Solving gives <m>x \approx -0.24559</m> or <m>x \approx 0.10696.</m>
        </p>
      </solution>
    </webwork>
  </exercise>

  <exercise xml:id="ex-1-1-4">
    <title>Solving a hidden quadratic equation again</title>
    <webwork>
      <pg-code>
        Context("Numeric");
        Context()->flags->set(tolType=>"absolute", tolerance=>0.001);
        
        $ans_small = Compute(-2.78585);
        $ans_large = Compute(0.78585);
      </pg-code>

      <statement>
        <p>
          Solve the quadratic equation
          <md>8(x+1)^2 - 3(x+1)^4 + 5 = 0</md>.
          Give your answer to at least three decimal places.
        </p>

       <p>
            Smaller solution:
            <var name = "$ans_small" width = "10"/>
        </p>

        <p>
            Larger solution:
            <var name = "$ans_large" width = "10"/>
        </p>
      </statement>

      <solution>
        <p>
            We can make a substitution <m>z = (x+1)^2</m>.  Then, we have <m>{8z - 3z^2 +5 = 0}</m>.  We can re-write this as <m>{3z^2 - 8z - 5 = 0.}</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            We can use the quadratic formula:
        </p>

        <p>
            <md> z = \frac{8 \pm \sqrt{64 + 60}}{6} \approx -0.52259, 3.18926.</md>
        </p>

        <p>
            Recall that <m>z=(x+1)^2</m>.  So, <m>(x+1)^2 = -0.52259</m> or <m>(x+1)^2 = 3.18926.</m>  
            This first gives non-real solutions.
            Solving <m>(x+1)^2 = 3.18926</m> gives <m>x \approx -2.78585</m> or <m>x \approx 0.78585.</m>
        </p>
      </solution>
    </webwork>
  </exercise>

  <exercise xml:id="ex-1-1-5">
    <title>Solving a hidden quadratic equation yet again</title>
    <webwork>
      <pg-code>
        Context("Numeric");
        Context()->flags->set(tolType=>"absolute", tolerance=>0.001);
        
        $ans = Compute(0.32143);
      </pg-code>

      <statement>
        <p>
          The moment generating function for a discrete random variable is given by <m>M_X(t) = 0.7e^{3t} + 0.3e^{6t}.</m>
          For which value is <m>M_X(t)</m> equal to 3.9?  Give your answer to at least three decimal places.
        </p>

       <p>
            Solution:
            <var name = "$ans" width = "10"/>
        </p>
      </statement>

      <solution>
        <p>
            We can make a substitution <m>z = e^{3t}</m>.  Then, we have <m>{0.7z + 0.3z^2 = 3.9}</m>.  We can re-write this as <m>{0.3z^2 + 0.7z - 3.9 = 0.}</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            We can use the quadratic formula:
        </p>

        <p>
            <md> z = \frac{-0.7 \pm \sqrt{0.49 + 4.68}}{0.6} \approx -4.95627, 2.62294.</md>
        </p>

        <p>
            Recall that <m>z=e^{3t}</m>.  So, <m>e^{3t} = -4.95627</m> or <m>e^{3t} = 2.62294.</m>  
            The first equation has no solution.
            Solving the second equation gives <m>t \approx 0.32143</m>.
        </p>
      </solution>
    </webwork>
  </exercise>
</subsection>